cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.CY

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) techniques applied to app reviews. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and ML applied to text data. The paper also discusses the impact of annotated data on the quality of ML models, which falls under the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper proposes changes to annotation guidelines, which is related to the sub-category of cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also discusses the trade-off between recall and precision, which is related to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with app reviews, which is related to the sub-category of cs.CY (Computers and Society).
